E8 reclassification (2026-05-24): the handler IS captured AND IS fired —
just AFTER a surviving `setTimeout(100)` that the test wasn't expecting.
The original framing — "lib defers emission via tickCallback which edge's
runtime doesn't drive" — is partly right (lib does defer via nextTick),
but the deeper issue is that `process.nextTick(emit)` doesn't drive
between `poll_oneoff` iterations on the wasm path.  See
experiments/e8-microtask-pump-spike/FINDINGS.md.

Still skipped pending an investigation of `process.nextTick` drive
timing in `lib/internal/process/promises.js`.
